          <h1>A Week in Review</h1>

          <p>
            This week I've been focusing on building my youtube brand and trying
            to put more effort into marketing my channel. I changed my youtube
            name from Web Dev Junkie to Web Dev Cody. I've been wanting to get
            my name in my channel and decided to do it before I got to 100k
            subscribers.
          </p>

          <p>
            One approach to improve the marketing is building out a newsletter
            management application which I can use to email my subscribers when
            I release new content. I also plan to use this newletter to promote
            any courses I may end up creating in the future.
          </p>

          <h2>A look into Astro</h2>

          <p>
            I setup a personal website using Astro. Overall, I think this
            framework easier to work with compared to Next.js. Don't get me
            wrong, next.js is great framework, but is can be a little confusing
            to learn at first. If you're looking into a simple way to create
            statically generated sites, Astro might be your solution. It has the
            power to create minimal webpages that contain zero javascript unless
            you manually add in interactivity.
          </p>

