          <h2>The Importance of Problem Solving</h2>

          <p>
            When you are first learning how to code, there are many challenges
            you will have to overcome. All of software involves problem solving.
            Some of the problems have been solved by others, but you'll still
            need to search google for those solutions and peice the puzzles
            together. Sometimes you'll run into problems you have to solve
            yourself. Overall, the only way to get great at coding is to
            practice solving more and more problems until most problems you
            encounter are ones you've solved in the past.
          </p>

          <p>
            Most larger problems are made up of smaller sub problems. Check out
            the following
            <a
              href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WXx9uidKm2w"
              target="_blank"
              >video</a
            >
            to get a better understand of how to break down a problem
          </p>

